lesdudis.caption: Gotta wear ‘em all! Absolutely love the new UNIQLO x Pokemon collection. This is UT’s first-ever collaboration with Pokemon TCG & the TCG Pocket app. Now available while supplies last.
Somewhere I belong… Hearing 16,000 people belt out “In The End” is a healing experience everyone should be a part of at least once in their lifetime. Linkin Park live is unreal!

Stories saw it first: The Nugget Spot’s Fried Chicken Ice Cream Sandwich. A sweet & savory summer sensation where spicy chicken heat meets cool chipotle ice cream in the perfect pairing. #LesDudisEats
A polka party at Madison Square Garden? Checked off the bucket list! Couldn’t have asked for a better first Weird Al concert: he totally brought down the house at his sold-out MSG debut!

Superman further cements James Gunn as the GOAT of on-screen comic book storytelling. It’s finally in theaters starting tonight and I can’t wait to re-experience all the best moments, this time in a Dolby Cinema! Go see it for yourself on the biggest screen possible. (This selfie is an oldie but a goodie from 2017.)

Hey NYC, eyes up here! Tonight’s IMAX screening of Superman was all kinds of super! We got collectible tickets, capes, posters, S emblem fans, and the best audience. Cannot wait to watch it again opening night this week! Thanks @IMAX!

Welcome… to Jurassic New York! To celebrate Jurassic World Rebirth now in theaters, catch this 5-story Titanosaurus at Rockefeller Center until July 5th! (Exclusive InGen badge courtesy of @dolbylabs today.)

Pokémon GO Fest: Jersey City is in the books! Thank you @pokemongoapp for the weekend access! Loved this year’s habitats, scenery, and the all-around vibes playing alongside the best community. Photos with Pikachu, new team swag, and lots more fun along the way… did you have a favorite GO Fest memory?
Annual GO Fest tradition with my bestie! Thank you @pokemongoapp for the weekend access!
There’s just something very a-𝐥𝐮𝐫𝐞-ing about the #PokémonGoFest2025 Mechanical Marvels habitat… Swipe through for a pass! Thank you @pokemongoapp for the weekend access!
A wild 🗽 appeared! Loved the views at Day 1 of #PokémonGoFest2025. Thank you @pokemongoapp for the weekend access!
Congratulations to Taylor Swift on her huge news today: getting back the rights to her recordings, music videos, art, and concert footage. Here’s my signed Red album to celebrate!
National Hamburger Day with retro vibes, courtesy of 8 Bit Bites! You won’t find a better combination of nostalgic eats, great prices, and classic gaming anywhere else in the city! #LesDudisEats

For the premiere of Andor Season 2’s final block of episodes, the Paley Center in NYC hosted a screening followed by a moderated discussion with Stephen Colbert, showrunner Tony Gilroy, and surprise guest Diego Luna. It was incredible hearing them talk about this masterpiece of a series. Let’s be clear: Andor isn’t just great Star Wars but it’s great media, period.
Another Simple Favor is coming to Prime Video on May 1 but we got to exclusively experience it on the big screen! If you loved the first film then the sequel will not disappoint!

Happy birthday @ChloeBennet! I got a chance to finally watch @InteriorChinatownHulu recently. Binged it, in fact, and I was hooked immediately because of Chloe, Jimmy O. Yang, & Ronny Chieng’s performances. Looking forward to the next convention tour for another moment like this one to talk about how good the series was!

Today marks 113 years since the sinking of The Titanic. Liberty Science Center’s Titanic: The Artifact Exhibition lets you step back in time to experience what it was like aboard the “unsinkable ship”. This interactive exhibition features more than 130 real artifacts, authentic room re-creations, and a chilled 7-foot-tall iceberg replica you can actually touch! Thank you to LSC for letting me check out this premium exhibition before it sets sail September 1.
Happy 60th birthday to the incredible & incomparable @RobertDowneyJr! Here’s an Iron Man comic he signed for me, witnessed & graded by CGC.
National Burrito Day can’t get much better than this: El Azteca’s Cod Fish Burrito! #LesDudisEats

Sad news hearing that Val Kilmer has died. Growing up, I watched Batman Forever more times than I can count. I listened to the audiobook on cassette whenever I couldn’t watch the movie. So meeting him in 2019 to get this signed was an unforgettable memory to say the least. He will be Batman forever. #RIPValKilmer
When you’re here, you’re family. Here at Zapp Con 6, that is!

Here’s an early look at Journey Together, the latest expansion from Scarlet & Violet, #sponsored by The Pokemon Company. I’m loving the ‘Trainer’s Pokemon’ cards and can’t wait to check out even more from this set! Thank you to the Pokemon Company for gifting me this product sneak peek. Journey Together will be available beginning March 28.

#PokemonTCG #PokemonCards #PokemonCardsOpening #PokemonCardOpening #JourneyTogether
It’s finally here! Who else is excited for Batman: H2SH? The team’s back for the sequel over 20 years later: Jeph Loeb, Jim Lee, Scott Williams, and Alex Sinclair. Can’t wait to dive in!

Last chance to check out some of the rarest & most iconic sports memorabilia at the Sotheby’s “Legend Of Sport” exhibition! In case you can’t make it, here are some of the highlights plus even more on the site (link in bio).
Every pizza is a personal pie if you believe in yourself… Happy Pi Day! #LesDudisEats
Here’s an exclusive first look at EVORETRO’s all-new Slab Binder along with other products they carry. If you’re searching for ways to organize and store your trading cards, check them out!
That’s a wrap on Toy Fair 2025!
The Pokémon booth at Toy Fair 2025 was a dream come true! I was blown away by the amazing displays, reveals, and surprises. Huge thanks to the Pokémon Company for this unforgettable visit!

The all-new Bandai Namco Cross Store is now open at Japan Village in Brooklyn, NY! This is the first of its kind in the U.S. and features all the divisions of Bandai Namco we know & love: One Piece TCG, model kits, Tamagotchi & Namco games, Tamashii Nations, nearly 200 Gashapon… and more! Read all about it on the site today (link in bio).

As a Karate Kid fan, I’ve loved @CobraKaiSeries since it premiered on YouTube Red in 2018. I just finished watching the final episodes on Netflix and there were so many great full circle moments & poetic payoffs, and an overall satisfying ending to its 6 season run. So glad I got to meet the original Karate Kids, @William_Zabka & @Ralph_Macchio to get this comic signed & slabbed!
